@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - mysql/MySqlDbSystem
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
state "provisioning\nprovider: CREATING, UPDATING" as provisioning
state "active\nprovider: ACTIVE" as active
state "updating\nprovider: UPDATING" as updating
state "failed\nprovider: repo-authored failure bucket" as failed
[*] --> provisioning : CreateDbSystem
provisioning --> active : ACTIVE
active --> updating : UpdateDbSystem
updating --> active : ACTIVE
provisioning --> failed : unresolved OCI error or\nopen gap
updating --> failed : unresolved OCI error or\nopen gap
failed --> [*] : operator intervention
note right of active
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Legacy-adapter controllers map
provider states into the shared controller
phases while open gaps keep additional
transitions explicit.
service: mysql
slug: mysqldbsystem
kind: MySqlDbSystem
archetype: legacy-adapter
status/finalizer: manual / none
requeue: provisioning, updating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
mutable/forceNew: access_mode,
backup_policy.copy_policies.backup_copy_retention_in_days,
backup_policy.copy_policies.copy_to_region,
backup_policy.defined_tags (+50 more) /
admin_password, admin_username,
availability_domain, compartment_id (+12 more)
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
delete-confirmation, endpoint-materialization,
legacy-adapter, list-lookup (+3 more)
Create reads username and password secrets
before submitting the OCI request.
Endpoint secret materialization only happens
after the DB system reaches ACTIVE.
Delete remains an unsupported legacy path, so no
confirmed terminating phase exists today.
end note
@enduml
